==> We can pass env variable while running container

# docker run -e APP_COLOR=blue img_name

==> How to find the env variable set on container thats already running
  $ docker inspect container_name


==> Run a container named blue-app using image kodekloud/simple-webapp and set the environment variable APP_COLOR to blue. 
Make the application available on port 38282 on the host. The application listens on port 8080.

 âžœ  docker run -d -e APP_COLOR=blue -p 38282:8080 --name blue-app kodekloud/simple-webapp
